review_blob: Keg @ The Earl of Essex. Great beer. You never would think that it is 9.3%. Full of hop aroma and sweet malts. They have managed to keep the taste full and the abv up without having the overpowering alcohol aftertaste that you get from so many of these beers. Not served too cold here either so you can get a real feel for the overall taste.
beer_name: Odell Myrcenary Double India Pale Ale

review_blob: Rating this as a lager. It stands out a a great modern beer. Adds a bit more taste than the usual and yet maintains its roots as the everyman go to pint.
